24:39.260 --> 24:41.001
So I hired Matt

24:41.044 --> 24:42.698
to be my best man.

24:42.742 --> 24:45.048
Make it look like
I know fancy people.

24:45.092 --> 24:48.051
Can I go back to my wedding now?

24:48.095 --> 24:50.227
Uh...Yeah, go ahead.

24:51.751 --> 24:54.797
You were arrested at the park
for fighting with Kevin.

24:54.841 --> 24:56.886
So why? Did he
owe you money? What?

24:56.930 --> 25:00.542
We were fighting because he
wouldn't do any drugs with me.

25:00.586 --> 25:03.719
Because that's the job
I was hired to do.

25:03.763 --> 25:08.202
So I-I don't understand.
So Kevin was your drug dealer?

25:08.245 --> 25:10.073
I'm an actor.
Times are tough.

25:10.117 --> 25:11.727
I was hired
to be Kevin's friend.

25:11.771 --> 25:13.381
Just like the groom.

25:13.424 --> 25:15.209
But instead of giving
best man speeches,

25:15.252 --> 25:17.733
I was supposed to keep him
nodding out.

25:17.777 --> 25:19.518
Eh, partying.

25:19.561 --> 25:22.564
Who hired you to carry out
this ridiculous charade?

25:22.608 --> 25:25.567
No idea. I-I got the job
through the agency

25:25.611 --> 25:26.960
that sets it all up.

25:27.003 --> 25:28.962
They're called Masquerade, Inc.

25:37.318 --> 25:38.624
[drops keys]

25:40.582 --> 25:44.238
Breaking and entering
will get you five years.

25:44.281 --> 25:46.283
You'd have to catch me first.

25:46.327 --> 25:50.287
So, you ready for me
to kill you yet?

25:50.331 --> 25:52.159
No. And you can
stop asking me.

25:52.202 --> 25:54.944
I'll let you know when
the brand is finally gone,

25:54.988 --> 25:56.467
but don't worry,
I think it's soon.

25:56.511 --> 25:57.904
Well, I did my part.

25:57.947 --> 25:59.993
So what are we thinking?

26:00.036 --> 26:03.649
Pain or no pain?No pain.

26:03.692 --> 26:05.302
I've had enough painful
death in my time.

26:05.346 --> 26:08.175
Let's keep this last one
quick and clean.

26:08.218 --> 26:10.394
No pain it is.

26:10.438 --> 26:12.092
Not for you anyhow.

26:14.398 --> 26:15.530
What?

26:15.574 --> 26:17.619
Decker's the one
who's gonna suffer.

26:17.663 --> 26:20.013
I got to admit, getting her
to fall for you, and then,

26:20.056 --> 26:24.539
poof, vanishing-- ruthless.

26:27.020 --> 26:29.762
And that's saying something
coming from a demon.

26:29.805 --> 26:31.111
Respect.

26:31.154 --> 26:33.548
I don't care who I have to hurt,

26:33.592 --> 26:35.463
as long as it allows me
to finally die.

26:40.250 --> 26:42.862
"No family? No friends?
No problem."

26:42.905 --> 26:44.385
And for a fee,
they'll send actors

26:44.428 --> 26:47.954
to pose as family or friends

26:47.997 --> 26:50.826
at public functions
for the sake of appearances.

26:50.870 --> 26:51.871
That's clever.Yeah, well,

26:51.914 --> 26:53.307
it's creepy.

26:53.350 --> 26:54.917
At least now we know
that whoever hired

26:54.961 --> 26:56.876
that exceptionally talented
actor from Bones

26:56.919 --> 26:59.966
may well be our killer. Hmm?

27:00.009 --> 27:02.359
So, um...
It says, says here

27:02.403 --> 27:04.971
the Masquerade office
is in Hollywood. I'm driving.

27:05.014 --> 27:07.538
Lucifer.

27:07.582 --> 27:10.063
I won't be able to get a warrant
until tomorrow morning.

27:10.106 --> 27:11.586
No. No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

27:11.630 --> 27:13.414
It-it is imperative
that we go now.

27:13.457 --> 27:15.242
It's imperative that you sleep.

27:15.285 --> 27:16.809
You clearly...

27:16.852 --> 27:18.245
I can't sleep!

27:21.596 --> 27:23.076
Detective, I can't sleep.

27:33.913 --> 27:35.741
[sighs]

27:37.090 --> 27:38.526
Lucifer.

27:40.049 --> 27:42.878
I've had it.What-- you won't
understand, really.

27:42.922 --> 27:45.533
Hmm?It's my wings. They're back.

27:45.576 --> 27:46.882
My Father, he's manipulating me.

27:46.926 --> 27:48.928
He's making me do things
that I would never do.

27:48.971 --> 27:50.799
What? Like flying
through the night,

27:50.843 --> 27:52.540
helping people
like some rogue angel?

27:52.583 --> 27:53.889
Yes! Yes, exactly!Uh-huh.

27:53.933 --> 27:56.718
That is the only
plausible explanation. [laughs]

27:56.762 --> 27:58.764
Either that or Linda's right,
and I'm suppressing

27:58.807 --> 28:01.462
pent-up feelings
about you and Pierce,

28:01.505 --> 28:03.725
which is obviously absurd.

28:03.769 --> 28:05.727
You hate that I'm with him.

28:05.771 --> 28:08.556
I couldn't care less that you're
with that insolent dullard.

28:08.599 --> 28:10.036
We both know that's not true,

28:10.079 --> 28:13.474
but what I want to know is why
it bothers you so much.

28:13.517 --> 28:17.739
Because, Detective, I happen
to know him better than you,

28:17.783 --> 28:19.741
and I know that
you can't trust him.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.090
Care to elaborate on that?

28:21.134 --> 28:23.440
I... Yeah.

28:23.484 --> 28:26.269
Fine, I will, because you
deserve to know the truth.Yes.

28:26.313 --> 28:28.054
Yes, okay.

28:28.097 --> 28:30.012
Pierce isn't Pierce.

28:30.056 --> 28:31.884
He's Kane from the Bible.

28:31.927 --> 28:33.624
And he's immortal.
He's been around for eons.

28:33.668 --> 28:35.539
And all he cares about
is ridding himself

28:35.583 --> 28:38.412
of that stupid curse
that my Father put on him...Stop.

28:38.455 --> 28:40.936
...because he killed
his brother.
Stop!

28:40.980 --> 28:43.460
You're tired, and you're
not thinking clearly.No...

28:43.504 --> 28:45.941
No, I'm-- it's not because
I'm tired, Detective!And...

28:45.985 --> 28:49.771
But since you
brought it up,

28:49.815 --> 28:54.297
let me tell you what
I think about Marcus.

28:54.341 --> 28:57.910
He is a good man

28:57.953 --> 28:59.302
who treats me right.

29:00.739 --> 29:03.437
And I'm happy, Lucifer.

29:03.480 --> 29:06.875
And all I know is how I feel
when I'm around him,

29:06.919 --> 29:09.095
and, you know, I l...

29:10.400 --> 29:11.619
I...

29:13.142 --> 29:15.754
We're done here.

29:23.239 --> 29:24.545
SALESMAN:
Seven carats

29:24.588 --> 29:26.677
of pure bliss.

29:26.721 --> 29:29.985
Don't you deserve
a little indulgence?

29:30.029 --> 29:31.160
I'll take it.

29:31.204 --> 29:33.336
[knock on door]Hey.

29:33.380 --> 29:34.642
You got a second?

29:34.685 --> 29:36.992
For you, Amenadiel, always.

29:37.036 --> 29:39.473
Don't go too far.

29:42.215 --> 29:46.567
Dan called me.
He's worried about you.

29:46.610 --> 29:50.310
Well, all is good.
In fact, it's better than good.

29:50.353 --> 29:51.659
It's perfect.

29:51.702 --> 29:54.009
Yeah, what about that
Spartan lifestyle?

29:54.053 --> 29:57.012
What can I say? Things change.

29:57.056 --> 29:58.405
And why is that?

29:58.448 --> 30:02.322
Because when you know
a pair of angels that can

30:02.365 --> 30:04.541
zip you up to Heaven
when the time comes,

30:04.585 --> 30:06.239
worrying is a waste of time.

30:10.547 --> 30:12.723
That's not how it works,
Charlotte.

30:12.767 --> 30:15.378
What do you mean?Okay, look.

30:15.422 --> 30:19.382
Neither I nor Lucifer have the
power to get anyone into Heaven.

30:19.426 --> 30:21.341
I don't have my wings,

30:21.384 --> 30:23.996
and Lucifer, well,

30:24.039 --> 30:26.389
he is, uh, most unwelcome.

30:26.433 --> 30:27.869
So the only thing
that matters,

30:27.913 --> 30:30.350
Charlotte, truly,
is who you are.

30:30.393 --> 30:32.874
It's okay.

30:32.918 --> 30:34.397
Nothing's changed.

30:34.441 --> 30:37.879
No, don't you see?
That's the problem.

30:37.923 --> 30:40.534
The second I thought
I had a free pass,

30:40.577 --> 30:42.753
an excuse not to be good,

30:42.797 --> 30:47.149
I relapsed into my old ways,

30:47.193 --> 30:49.630
into who I really am.

30:54.635 --> 30:57.029
There's no hope for me.

30:57.072 --> 30:59.553
Amenadiel, I can't change.

31:02.643 --> 31:05.646
I'm going to Hell.

31:07.430 --> 31:09.563
[gasps]

31:16.918 --> 31:18.572
Mommy.
CHLOE:
Hmm?

31:18.615 --> 31:20.443
Did you know if you're
ever mean to me,

31:20.487 --> 31:22.924
I can just go on this site
and order a new mommy?

31:22.968 --> 31:25.144
Oh, yeah? How you
gonna pay for that?

31:25.187 --> 31:26.580
Your credit card.

31:26.623 --> 31:29.278
I've gotten pretty good
at your signature, you know.

31:29.322 --> 31:31.802
I don't doubt that.
All right, come on.

31:31.846 --> 31:33.587
Let's go get some
pizza and ice cream

31:33.630 --> 31:34.805
on the way home.

31:34.849 --> 31:35.981
[mouthing]

31:37.156 --> 31:38.113
He seems nice.

31:38.157 --> 31:41.856
He is nice. You know, Monkey,

31:41.900 --> 31:43.684
since Daddy,

31:43.727 --> 31:48.254
I haven't really dated anyone...
well, seriously.

31:48.297 --> 31:49.342
And, uh...

31:49.385 --> 31:50.952
Marcus and I,

31:50.996 --> 31:53.781
we've been spending
a lot of time together.

31:53.824 --> 31:57.350
And the truth is...
I like him, a lot.

31:57.393 --> 32:01.267
And it's just so important to me
that you're okay with that.

32:01.310 --> 32:03.356
Is he the reason
you've been so happy lately?

32:06.315 --> 32:07.838
I think so.

32:07.882 --> 32:10.319
Does he like chocolate cake?

32:10.363 --> 32:11.842
You know what,
I don't know.

32:11.886 --> 32:13.235
Let's ask him.

32:15.281 --> 32:16.891
All right.
[clears throat]

32:18.893 --> 32:20.025
Oh, my God.

32:22.070 --> 32:23.637
What is it, Mommy?

32:23.680 --> 32:25.334
That's Jeremy Bell.

32:25.378 --> 32:27.989
The husband we interviewed.

32:28.033 --> 32:30.035
Hello?

32:32.385 --> 32:34.865
[wind whistling]

32:34.909 --> 32:38.478
Anyone there?

32:46.616 --> 32:49.228
LUCIFER:
Trouble sleeping?

32:59.760 --> 33:01.240
Mr. Morningstar,
what are you doing here?

33:01.283 --> 33:04.373
Shh. It's probably best
not to wake your family.

33:04.417 --> 33:08.029
Even though...

33:08.073 --> 33:09.683
they're not your family.

33:09.726 --> 33:11.206
I just came
from Masquerade

33:11.250 --> 33:14.122
where a most cooperative
employee

33:14.166 --> 33:16.559
helped me connect the dots.

33:16.603 --> 33:19.562
So, you used to be an actor.

33:19.606 --> 33:21.695
We're in L.A., everybody
used to be an actor.

33:21.738 --> 33:24.698
Mm-hmm, but not everyone gets
such a cushy gig, do they?

33:24.741 --> 33:26.004
Your so-called wife

33:26.047 --> 33:29.790
worried she'd no longer
fit in with the classes

33:29.833 --> 33:33.272
after she broke it off
with her deadbeat baby daddy,

33:33.315 --> 33:36.101
hired you to play
husband and father.

33:36.144 --> 33:38.886
Murdering to keep the gig?

33:38.929 --> 33:40.975
That seems a tad method,
don't you think?

33:41.019 --> 33:42.107
Murder?

33:42.150 --> 33:43.934
Th-That's crazy.

33:43.978 --> 33:45.371
All right, look,
you need to leave

33:45.414 --> 33:46.546
or I'm gonna call the police.

33:46.589 --> 33:48.939
Oh, please.
Spare me the theatrics

33:48.983 --> 33:50.593
because I am in no mood

33:50.637 --> 33:52.769
to hear the half-baked
recitation of innocence

33:52.813 --> 33:56.121
by a, well, mediocre actor.

34:02.431 --> 34:04.303
Was it mediocre acting

34:04.346 --> 34:07.436
that got Mary to actually
fall in love with me?

34:07.480 --> 34:10.091
And Kevin's reappearance
just put all that in jeopardy.

34:10.135 --> 34:11.919
Yeah, I wasn't about
to let that loser

34:11.962 --> 34:14.487
weasel his way back in here.

34:14.530 --> 34:16.837
Just like I'm not gonna let you
mess it up, either.

34:16.880 --> 34:19.622
[chuckles]Too bad you're trespassing.

34:19.666 --> 34:21.059
[grunts]

34:22.321 --> 34:23.757
What the hell?

34:23.800 --> 34:25.193
Most kind of you
to admit your guilt.

34:25.237 --> 34:26.629
The trying to kill me part,
less so.

34:26.673 --> 34:28.022
Aah!

34:28.066 --> 34:30.938
Now, tell me what
I really want to know.

34:30.981 --> 34:33.767
Am I the angel?
What angel?!

34:33.810 --> 34:35.160
Did I stop you
from killing that old woman?

34:35.203 --> 34:37.249
What happened the night
you killed Kevin?!

34:37.292 --> 34:38.815
Okay. I'll tell you.

34:38.859 --> 34:39.816
After I shot him, I ran out.

34:39.860 --> 34:41.644
I bumped into that old lady.

34:41.688 --> 34:43.472
But there was
nobody else there.

34:43.516 --> 34:45.648
She fell into some kind of
religious trance so I bolted!

34:45.692 --> 34:46.649
She saw an angel!

34:46.693 --> 34:49.130
Was it me?!
No! I...

34:49.174 --> 34:52.133
It was a-a shadow
from-from those figurines.

34:52.177 --> 34:54.135
With the figurines, the angel
figurines. Did you plant

34:54.179 --> 34:55.180
the figurine
in my bedroom?!
No, no.

34:55.223 --> 34:56.877
I-I touched one of them.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.271
So I took it, but it had
my prints on it.

34:59.314 --> 35:00.663
I destroyed it right
after. I swear.

35:00.707 --> 35:03.840
Then... how...

35:03.884 --> 35:05.015
[grunts]

35:06.104 --> 35:10.543
I was only trying
to protect my family.

35:10.586 --> 35:13.328
It was never your family
to protect,

35:13.372 --> 35:15.069
you pathetic imposter.

35:15.113 --> 35:16.201
You stole it

35:16.244 --> 35:17.985
from Kevin Winstead.

35:18.028 --> 35:20.379
And then you kept him distracted

35:20.422 --> 35:22.859
by hiring someone
to keep the party going.

35:22.903 --> 35:25.384
Driving him
to self-destruction,

35:25.427 --> 35:29.910
stoking the very fires
of his own weakness...

35:31.564 --> 35:33.131
...to keep him out of the way.

35:34.393 --> 35:36.090
How could I be so blind?

35:47.928 --> 35:50.409
Jeremy Bell? LAPD.

35:54.413 --> 35:56.763
It's all my fault.

35:57.938 --> 35:59.722
I killed Kevin Winstead.

36:01.942 --> 36:03.596
I am a pathetic imposter.

36:12.257 --> 36:13.345
[elevator bell dings]

36:15.608 --> 36:17.218
What are you doing?

36:17.262 --> 36:18.567
I need to find it, Maze.

36:18.611 --> 36:20.134
Find what?

36:20.178 --> 36:21.440
Your self-respect?

36:21.483 --> 36:23.746
The-the angel figurine.
It's here somewhere.

36:23.790 --> 36:26.053
I-I need to find it
so that I can

36:26.096 --> 36:28.838
convince the detective
that Pierce...

36:28.882 --> 36:30.710
isn't who she thinks he is.

36:30.753 --> 36:32.625
What? I don't understand.
Explain.

36:32.668 --> 36:34.540
I figured it out, haven't I?

36:34.583 --> 36:36.846
Pierce has been
gaslighting me.

36:36.890 --> 36:38.065
He's been tricking me
into thinking

36:38.108 --> 36:40.763
I've been doing good deeds
in my sleep.

36:40.807 --> 36:41.895
Why would he do that?

36:41.938 --> 36:43.505
Because...

36:43.549 --> 36:44.898
to keep me away
from the detective

36:44.941 --> 36:46.900
so he can pursue her.

36:46.943 --> 36:48.815
He must be back to thinking
that she's the key to lifting

36:48.858 --> 36:50.077
his bloody curse.

36:50.120 --> 36:51.121
I mean, I tried to warn her,

36:51.165 --> 36:53.123
but she wouldn't
listen, would she?

36:53.167 --> 36:54.516
And why wouldn't she listen?

36:54.560 --> 36:56.257
Because the detective
always needs proof.

36:56.301 --> 36:58.912
And what better proof than
that trinket that he used

36:58.955 --> 37:01.480
to-to-to deceive me?

37:02.655 --> 37:03.960
[laughs]

37:05.223 --> 37:06.485
Wait.

37:08.313 --> 37:09.314
If you want Chloe
to believe you,

37:09.357 --> 37:12.273
you have to do it right.

37:12.317 --> 37:14.797
Take it to Ellen.
Have her do her lab thingy.

37:14.841 --> 37:16.321
Yes, yes, you're right.

37:16.364 --> 37:19.802
First, back up.
Tell me everything.

37:19.846 --> 37:21.848
Start at the beginning.

37:21.891 --> 37:23.458
And don't leave
a single thing out.

37:23.502 --> 37:26.156
It's just...

37:26.200 --> 37:30.160
so hard to put everything
together in my mind, Maze.

37:30.204 --> 37:31.510
I mean, you-you
wouldn't understand.

37:32.641 --> 37:33.642
Thank you.

37:33.686 --> 37:34.774
That's very kind of you.

37:40.388 --> 37:43.478
Which is not like you at all.

37:43.522 --> 37:44.784
Why are you even here?

37:46.046 --> 37:49.005
You're helping him.
Aren't you?

37:49.049 --> 37:51.878
"Helping him"?

37:51.921 --> 37:54.533
This was myidea.

37:55.708 --> 37:58.493
After Pierce told me

37:58.537 --> 38:00.974
about that old lady who
thought she saw an angel,

38:01.017 --> 38:04.369
that's when it all
came together.

38:06.371 --> 38:11.419
I planted the figurine
by your bed.

38:11.463 --> 38:16.685
My neck... is still jacked
from wearing those fake wings

38:16.729 --> 38:17.860
to save that dumb family

38:17.904 --> 38:19.558
in San Bernardino.

38:19.601 --> 38:23.039
You came this close
the other night to waking up

38:23.083 --> 38:25.041
after I took those
handcuffs off.

38:25.085 --> 38:28.349
Thankfully, handcuffs in bed,
I got that.

38:28.393 --> 38:30.917
Why would you do this to me,
Mazikeen?

38:32.919 --> 38:35.182
Because I know
the only thing

38:35.225 --> 38:37.315
that matters to you
more than Chloe.

38:38.403 --> 38:40.709
You.

38:40.753 --> 38:42.885
Easiest way to spin you out.

38:42.929 --> 38:45.279
Tap into those daddy issues.

38:45.323 --> 38:47.673
"I can't get rid
of my wings.

38:47.716 --> 38:50.719
Daddy's controlling me."

38:50.763 --> 38:54.375
Wah, wah, wah.

38:54.419 --> 38:56.943
[laughs]
You're stalling me.

38:56.986 --> 38:58.727
Aren't you?
[laughs]

38:58.771 --> 39:01.556
I need to get to
the detective!

39:01.600 --> 39:06.561
â™ª Well, if you told me
you were drowning â™ª

39:06.605 --> 39:10.870
â™ª I would not lend a hand

39:10.913 --> 39:15.222
â™ª I've seen your face before,
my friend... â™ª

39:15.265 --> 39:17.398
[knocking on door]

39:17.442 --> 39:19.400
Hi.

39:19.444 --> 39:21.271
What do you have?

39:21.315 --> 39:24.536
You're lucky you're cute

39:24.579 --> 39:27.930
because I hate surprises.

39:27.974 --> 39:29.062
Come on.

39:29.105 --> 39:30.237
Let me see.

39:30.280 --> 39:31.934
To celebrate solving a murder.

39:31.978 --> 39:33.762
[gasps]

39:33.806 --> 39:36.286
Mm, my second favorite
kind of six-pack.

39:36.330 --> 39:39.115
[chuckles]
Thank you.

39:39.159 --> 39:41.204
And this.

39:41.248 --> 39:43.555
I'm more of a key
lime pie guy myself,

39:43.598 --> 39:46.558
but every proper bribe
requires self-sacrifice.

39:46.601 --> 39:48.473
Trixie is
gonna love this.

39:48.516 --> 39:49.604
It's her favorite.
Hmm.

39:49.648 --> 39:50.779
She's at a birthday party
right now.

39:50.823 --> 39:52.346
Oh, birthday party.

39:52.390 --> 39:53.782
Maybe she's already had
enough cake for the evening.

39:53.826 --> 39:58.874
Well, then maybe we can
all share it together

39:58.918 --> 40:00.572
tomorrow morning
for breakfast.

40:00.615 --> 40:02.791
You mean I don't have to sneak
out of the house in the morning

40:02.835 --> 40:03.966
